data.chText: 使人不舒服的；令人不舒适的
data.enText: not letting you feel physically comfortable; unpleasant to wear, sit on, etc.

data.chText: 这床太不舒服了，我睡不着觉。
data.enText: I couldn't sleep because the bed was so uncomfortable.

data.chText: 感到难受的；感觉不舒服（或不暖和等）的
data.enText: not feeling physically relaxed, warm, etc.

data.chText: 我坐着的姿势难受极了。
data.enText: I was sitting in an extremely uncomfortable position.

data.chText: 她不扶东西站着仍觉得不舒服。
data.enText: She still finds it uncomfortable to stand without support.

data.chText: （使）焦虑的，尴尬的，害怕的，不自在的
data.enText: anxious, embarrassed or afraid and unable to relax; making you feel like this

data.chText: 提到这个话题，他显然局促不安起来。
data.enText: He looked distinctly uncomfortable when the subject was mentioned.

data.chText: 有一种令人不安的寂静。
棘手的；麻烦的；难处理的
data.enText: unpleasant or difficult to deal with

data.chText: 我内心惴惴不安，觉得那是我的过错。
data.enText: I had the uncomfortable feeling that it was my fault.

simple_means.memory_skill: un 不 + comfortable 舒适的 → 不舒服的

means: 感觉不舒服(或不暖和等)的

example: an uncomfortable day in the hot sun

tr: conducive to or feeling mental discomfort
example: this kind of life can prove disruptive and uncomfortable
grew uncomfortable beneath his appraising eye
an uncomfortable way of surprising me just when I felt surest
the teacher's presence at the conference made the child very uncomfortable

value.def: If you are uncomfortable, you are slightly worried or embarrassed, and not relaxed and confident.

example.ex: The request for money made them feel uncomfortable...
example.tran: 索要金钱让他们有些不安。

example.ex: If you are uncomfortable with your counsellor or therapist, you must discuss it...
example.tran: 如果面对咨询顾问或治疗师时你觉得不自在，一定要提出来。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>with/about</l> n, ADJ -ing

value.tran: 不自在的；不安的；尴尬的

example.ex: Sandy leaned across the table, his face uncomfortably close to Brad's...
example.tran: 桑迪探过桌子，他的脸跟布拉德的脸靠得异常地近。

example.ex: I became uncomfortably aware that the people at the next table were watching me...
example.tran: 觉察到邻桌的人在看我，我感到很不自在。

value.def: Something that is uncomfortable makes you feel slight pain or physical discomfort when you experience it or use it.

example.ex: Wigs are hot and uncomfortable to wear constantly...
example.tran: 头上老是顶着假发，又热又不舒服。

example.ex: The Metro journey back to the centre of the town was hot and uncomfortable.
example.tran: 乘地铁返回市中心又热又不舒服。

value.def: If you are uncomfortable, you are not physically content and relaxed, and feel slight pain or discomfort.

example.ex: I sometimes feel uncomfortable after eating in the evening...
example.tran: 我晚上吃完饭有时会觉得不舒服。

example.ex: People living or working with smokers can find it uncomfortable to wear contact lenses because the smoke causes irritation.
example.tran: 与吸烟者一起生活或工作的人会发现戴隐形眼镜不舒服，因为烟具有刺激作用。

example.ex: He awoke to find himself lying uncomfortably on a pile of firewood.
example.tran: 他醒来发现自己躺在一堆柴火上，很不舒服。

value.def: You can describe a situation or fact as uncomfortable when it is difficult to deal with and causes problems and worries.

example.ex: It is uncomfortable to think of our own death, but we need to...
example.tran: 想到人终有一死会感到不舒服，但我们不得不去面对。

example.ex: Such questions are uncomfortable to answer...
example.tran: 这些问题让人很难回答。

example.ex: The decree put the president in an uncomfortable position.
example.tran: 这一判决使总统陷入了尴尬的处境中。

gramarinfo.label: oft <l>it</l> v-link ADJ to-inf, ADJ to-inf

value.tran: （处境、事实等）令人不快的，令人担忧的，令人不安的
